[0.000, "o", "Dynamic Extensions ;\r\u001b[24d;"]
[0.000, "o", ";;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\u001b[25d"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[26d; "]
[0.000, "o", "If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\r\u001b[27d"]
[0.000, "o", "; syntax:\u001b[28;3H\u001b[K\u001b[29d"]
[0.000, "o", "  extension=modulename\u001b[K\r\u001b[30d"]
[0.000, "o", ";\u001b[31d "]
[0.000, "o", "For example:\u001b[K\u001b[32;3H\u001b[K\r\u001b[33d"]
[0.000, "o", ";   \u001b[30m\u001b[43mextension=mysql\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000fi\u001b[34;3H\u001b[K\u001b[35dWhen the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[36;3Hdirectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\r\u001b[37d;\u001b[38d   extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[K\u001b[39;3H\u001b[K\u001b[40dNote : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[K\r\u001b[41d"]
[0.000, "o", "; 'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\r\u001b[42d;"]
[0.000, "o", " deprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\u001b[43;3Hmove to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\r\u001b[44d;"]
