[0.000, "o", "<IfModule unixd_module>\u001b[K\r\u001b[36d#"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[37d\b"]
[0.000, "o", "# If you wish httpd to run as a different user or group, you must run\r\u001b[38d#"]
[0.000, "o", " httpd as root initially and it will switch.\u001b[K\r\u001b[39d#"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[40d"]
[0.001, "o", " User/Group: The name (or #number) of the user/group to run httpd as.\r\u001b[41d#"]
[0.000, "o", " It is usually good practice to create a dedicated user and group for\r\u001b[42d# running httpd, as with most system services.\u001b[K\r\u001b[43d#\u001b[K\u001b[44d\bUser http\u001b[K\r\u001b[45dGroup http\u001b[K\r\u001b[46d\u001b[K\u001b[47d"]
[0.000, "o", "</IfModule>\u001b[K\r\u001b[48d\u001b[K\u001b[49d#"]
[0.000, "o", " 'Main' server configuration\u001b[K\r\u001b[50d#\u001b[K\u001b[51d"]
[0.000, "o", " The directives in this section set up the values used by the 'main'\r\u001b[52d#"]
[0.000, "o", " server, which responds to any requests that aren't handled by a\r\u001b[53d#"]
[0.000, "o", " <VirtualHost> definition.  These values also provide defaults for\r\u001b[54d#"]
[0.000, "o", " any <VirtualHost> containers you may define later in the file.\r\u001b[55d#"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[56d"]
[0.000, "o", " All of these directives may appear inside <VirtualHost> containers,\r\u001b[57d#"]
[0.000, "o", " in which case these default settings will be overridden for the\u001b[K\r\u001b[58d#"]
[0.000, "o", " virtual host being defined.\u001b[K\r\u001b[59d#"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[60d\b\u001b[K\u001b[61d"]
[0.000, "o", "#\u001b[K\u001b[62d"]
[0.000, "o", " ServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be\r\u001b[63d#"]
[0.000, "o", " e-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\r\u001b[64d# as error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\r\u001b[33d#"]
